song_name: The Place Where The Rivers Run

version_description: Title track from Runrig,s final studio album of the same name in 2016,best played with acoustic guitar with plucked strings,bar the chorus which can be strummed,i have added English translation of Gaelic lyric.

Originally recorded on the 1995 Mara album and re released on the 2018 album The One That Got Away.With an uptempo rock beat i think it sounds good using electric acoustic guitar with reverb,chorus effects.You Tube:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tIbS6woCrtY.
From the 2016 album,The Story,i find playing with acoustic guitar better,verses can be plucked whilst chorus strummed.As an alternative Electric "clean" guitar could be used.
Simple tune,kept simple set in the key of G,no capo required best played on acoustic guitar.
Electric Guitar Clean Overdrive/Chorus effects medium folk/rock beat https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nVVDgBgwykk.

song_name: This Is Not A Love Song

version_description: Track from the Runrig 2018 farewell album The Ones That Got Away .Originally recorded in 1986 and again in 1994 as a festive homecoming.Best played with acoustic guitar simply plucked or steady strum.You Tube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qlUY2CzRJaw.
Best played on Electric/acoustic guitar with clean sound,no capo required.This is the original album version,some of the live recordings used elcectric guitar with chorus/tremolo sound.

song_name: Blame It On The Fire In My Heart
